Narrative: We are excited to offer a comprehensive tutoring program designed to equip high school students with the fundamental skills necessary for success on the ACT  exams. Our program focuses on building a strong academic foundation, ensuring students are well-prepared for these crucial standardized tests. We believe in empowering young minds to achieve their full potential, paving the way for future educational and career opportunities. Each session of our tutoring program spans 8 weeks, providing a consistent and structured learning environment. During this time, students will engage with experienced tutors who specialize in the core subjects tested on both the ACT . We utilize proven teaching methodologies and personalized instruction to address individual learning needs, helping students strengthen their understanding and boost their confidence. By focusing on fundamental skills and providing dedicated support, we aim to enhance students' test-taking abilities and open doors to higher education and military service. Join us at the Red Shield Youth Center and take the first step towards a brighter future!
Whattobring: All materials will be provided to the participants.
TransportationFeeandDetails:
Ensuring your child's safe and convenient transportation to our after-school program is a top priority for us.​ We understand the importance of reliable pick-up services, allowing families peace of mind and consistent participation in our enriching activities.

To facilitate easy access for our members, we are pleased to offer complimentary pick-up services directly from several local schools. Our dedicated staff will be available to transport students from Booker T. Washington. Students must arrange for transportation to take them home. 

These pick-up services are consistently provided Monday through Friday, promptly at 3:00 PM. We are committed to making your child's journey to the Red Shield Youth Center as smooth and stress-free as possible.

Narrative:
Every Tuesday is Club Day at The Salvation Army Red Shield Youth Center, and it’s one of our favorite parts of the week! Students get to explore music, arts, STEM, games, self-defense and creative expression in a fun, supportive environment designed to build confidence, teamwork, and hands-on skills.

From rhythm games and instrument basics to drawing, painting, science, and creative crafting, Tuesday Club Days give our members the chance to discover new interests and talents. Activities are tailored for elementary ages and led by caring staff and volunteers who encourage imagination, positive peer interactions, and a love of the arts.

Club Days help children develop:

  • Confidence and self-expression

  • Fine motor and listening skills

  • Teamwork and communication

  • Creative problem solving

  • Appreciation for music, movement, and visual arts

We believe creativity strengthens the whole child — and Tuesday Club Days bring that joy to life each week!

Narrative:
Join us after school for a fun, engaging, and supportive environment where kids can learn, play, and grow!
      The Red Shield Youth Center's after-school program provides a dynamic and nurturing place for children and teenagers, grounded in Christian principles. Here, young minds are encouraged to discover their talents and grow holistically through a rich tapestry of activities that extend far beyond the typical school day. It’s a dedicated space for fostering intellectual curiosity, personal development, and a strong sense of community.

    Our comprehensive approach ensures every participant finds their niche. Budding scientists and engineers can delve into exciting STEM challenges, sparking critical thinking and innovation. Creative spirits can flourish in engaging arts programs, while dedicated homework help sessions ensure academic success. To round out their development, athletic programs build physical prowess and teach invaluable lessons in teamwork and sportsmanship.

    Beyond skill acquisition, the program emphasizes character formation, guided by mentorship and leadership opportunities. Older participants gain valuable experience by guiding their younger peers, cultivating responsibility and a spirit of service. This entire journey unfolds within a Christian framework, instilling core values of compassion, integrity, and community, empowering youth to build a brighter future for themselves and others.
Whattobring: All materials will be provided for the kids.
OrientationDetails: Parents must complete a short training before their child can attend.
TransportationFeeandDetails: Transportation will be provided from several neighborhood schools. Transportation will be provided from JS Clark, Judson ,Midway and Oak Park.

Narrative:
Looking for a safe, enriching place for your child after school? Our Christ-centered Afterschool Program runs Monday through Friday and serves students Kindergarten through 8th grade, offering families peace of mind and kids a place to grow, learn, and thrive.

Each afternoon is thoughtfully structured to support the whole child—mind, body, and spirit. Students enjoy a daily devotional, a healthy snack, homework help, and engaging structured activities, followed by supervised playtime in the gym or outdoors. With no screen time, children are encouraged to build creativity, confidence, friendships, and strong character in a positive, faith-filled environment.

Our caring staff creates a welcoming space where kids feel supported, valued, and excited to come each day. The program runs until 6:00 PM, making it a dependable option for working families. Students are picked up from school by bus and transported back to our center daily. For a list of schools currently served or additional details, please contact peyton.sealy@uss.salvationarmy.org.

Cost: $60 per week
An affordable, purposeful afterschool experience where faith, fun, and learning come together. Daily devotional, snack, homework help, structured activities, and screen-free play.

Narrative:
Youth Nights & Character Building

Youth Nights at our after-school program are rooted in The Salvation Army’s Character Building Curriculum, a trusted program designed to help young people grow spiritually, socially, emotionally, and academically in a safe and supportive environment.

During Youth Nights, participants are grouped by age and take part in structured character-building programs including Adventure Corps, Moonbeams, Sunbeams, and Girl Guards. Each program is intentionally designed to meet youth at their developmental level while teaching core values such as respect, responsibility, kindness, teamwork, leadership, and service to others.

Every Youth Night includes interactive lessons, hands-on activities, group discussions, games, and creative projects that reinforce positive decision-making and healthy relationships. Youth are encouraged to explore their strengths, build confidence, and develop life skills that support success at home, in school, and in the community.

Our trained staff and volunteers foster an inclusive and encouraging atmosphere where youth feel safe to be themselves, ask questions, and grow. Through consistent routines and caring mentorship, Youth Nights help children form meaningful connections while learning how their actions impact others.

Youth Nights are more than an after-school activity—they are an opportunity for young people to build character, strengthen faith-based values, and develop the tools they need to become confident, compassionate leaders of tomorrow.
